OL,6,FShe believed that the colleague would
OL,7,Fnot be returning to work. She was then
OL,8,Fadvised that they would be returning
OL,9,Fto their role. Ms Hermosilla has found
OL,10,Fthe whole process and its outcome very
OL,11,Fupsetting and distressing.
OL,13,FMs Hermosilla also advised her
OL,14,Femployer of comments made to her by
OL,15,Fthe same colleague of a racial and
OL,16,Fpolitical nature, which she also found
OL,17,Fto be inappropriate. This was also
OL,18,Finvestigated by her employer.
OL,20,FThe cases were settled without
OL,21,Fadmission of liability.
